HEADWORD: Goodliness
<hw>Good"li*ness</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Goodly</er>.]</ety> <def>Beauty of form; grace; elegance;
comeliness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Her <qex>goodliness</qex> was full of harmony to his eyes.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir P. Sidney.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Good-looking</ent>⟦br⟧
